The `m_nodes_copy{m_connman.vNodes}` in the initializer list is accessing `vNodes` without the `cs_vNodes` lock. You could update it to take the lock:

```diff
diff --git a/src/net.cpp b/src/net.cpp
index 6040ee86be..d39aa14b20 100644
--- a/src/net.cpp
+++ b/src/net.cpp
@@ -117,7 +117,9 @@ std::string strSubVersion;
 class NodesSnapshot
 {
     public:
-        explicit NodesSnapshot(const CConnman& connman) : m_connman{connman}, m_nodes_copy{m_connman.vNodes}
+        explicit NodesSnapshot(const CConnman& connman) :
+            m_connman{connman},
+            m_nodes_copy{WITH_LOCK(m_connman.cs_vNodes, return m_connman.vNodes;)}
         {
             LOCK(m_connman.cs_vNodes);
             for (auto& node : m_nodes_copy) {
```

But that would introduce a race condition if another thread deleted a node between the initializer list and the ctor being run.

I think better just to assign `m_nodes_copy` in the ctor.

